<subSubSection id="02C66578FFFCFFBDFF3D98EB68DB7807" pageId="17" pageNumber="31" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFFCFFBDFF3D98EB68847986" blockId="17.[151,756,1199,1382]" pageId="17" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFFCFFBDFF3D98EB680579A6" bold="true" box="[151,264,1199,1223]" pageId="17" pageNumber="31">Remarks:</emphasis>
It is characterized by its subcylindrical shape and inflated chambers.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFFCFFBDFF3D98AA68DB7807" blockId="17.[151,756,1199,1382]" pageId="17" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFFCFFBDFF3D98AA68D87867" bold="true" box="[151,469,1262,1286]" pageId="17" pageNumber="31">Stratigraphic distribution:</emphasis>
It is recorded in the Maastrichtian and Paleocene zones but its range may be extended to the Early Eocene as recorded in LE ROY, 1953 and in the present study.
</paragraph>
